Title: Unstable Systems in Relativistic Quantum Field Theory

Authors: L. Maiani, M. Testa

Comments: 12 pages, Latex

Journal-ref: Annals Phys. 263 (1998) 353-367

We show how the state of an unstable particle can be defined in terms ofstable asymptotic states. This general definition is used to discuss and tosolve some old problems connected with the short-time and large-time behaviourof the non-decay amplitude.